"I swear, it feels like it‚Äôs getting worse," Tom muttered as he adjusted the collar of his jacket, his breath misting in the cold air as he moved through the dim corridors.

"It‚Äôs just the storm," Claire replied, but her voice was tinged with unease. "It‚Äôs fine."

But as they passed by the old fountain in the food court, they all stopped in their tracks. The fountain, which had been dry for as long as anyone could remember, was now leaking water‚Äîa slow trickle that ran down the side and pooled in the cracks of the stone basin. It wasn‚Äôt flowing, not in the traditional sense, but the steady drip was enough to catch their attention.

"That... wasn‚Äôt like that earlier," Dave said, frowning as he took a step closer to inspect the fountain.

