"It‚Äôs the storm," Dave insisted, though even he sounded unsure. "We‚Äôll check the back later, but for now, let‚Äôs not jump to conclusions. Could just be a weird coincidence."

They all stood for a moment, watching the water leak slowly into the fountain‚Äôs basin. The sound of the dripping water echoed louder than it should have, the soft plink of each drop hitting the stone floor unnerving in its stillness.

"It‚Äôs strange, but I‚Äôm not gonna worry about it unless it gets worse," Claire said, turning back to the hallway. "We‚Äôve got other places to check."

They moved on, but the sound of water dripping was now lodged in the back of their minds. It wasn‚Äôt a major issue‚Äînothing that needed immediate attention. Still, the fountain‚Äôs sudden change from dry to leaky was unsettling, especially considering its history of being unused for years.

