Sean, who had been sitting silently, stared at the monitors. He didn‚Äôt respond at first. His eyes were locked on the camera feed for the arcade on the second floor. The mall‚Äôs arcade had been shut down for years, the machines abandoned and unused. But tonight, something was different.

One of the arcade machines on the screen had turned on.

