A terrifying silence filled the room. The shaking of the door ceased, and the sound of the wind howling outside was the only thing left. The only evidence that something had happened was the lingering sense of dread that hung in the air like smoke.

Claire and Brett stood still, staring at the door. Neither of them dared to move.

After what felt like an eternity, Brett spoke in a hoarse whisper.

‚ÄúWhat... what the hell just happened?‚Äù

Claire didn‚Äôt answer right away. She was too afraid to speak, her mind reeling from what she had just heard. She stared at the door, waiting for something‚Äîanything‚Äîto happen. But there was nothing. The door remained quiet, the only sound the soft echo of the storm outside.

"I don‚Äôt know," Claire finally whispered, her voice trembling. "But we need to get out. Now."

Brett didn‚Äôt argue. They both knew it was time to leave.

